# BrainSpace AI: Core Workspace Architecture

This plan outlines the upgrade of our workspace into a production-grade Notion clone, migrating away from standard API routes to Next.js 16 Server Actions, and strictly enforcing Server-first component patterns.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Moving to Server Actions means we will delete the previous `/api/documents` REST routes. All mutations will now happen via type-safe server functions that trigger `revalidatePath()`.

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **Recent Pages Tracking**: Should "Recents" track what an *individual user* has clicked on (requires a new `ViewHistory` database table), or just show the most recently updated documents across the entire workspace?
> 2. **Cover Images**: Do you want users to upload cover images (requires AWS S3 / Vercel Blob setup), or just provide a URL/Unsplash integration for now?

